#. type: Title =
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Black & white conversion\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:6
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tool-Black_and_White-en.png) The **Black & White** tool "
"allows you to convert a color photo into a black-and-white photo."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:9
msgid ""
"Additionally, you can control the conversion as if a colored filter were "
"placed in front of the lens when the photo was taken."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note:** A filter of a certain color actually filters out its\n"
"*complementary* color (the color directly across from it in the color\n"
"wheel).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:18
msgid ""
"For example, a yellow filter filters out blue light (because blue is "
"directly across from yellow). Therefore, you can usually increase contrast "
"in the sky by using a yellow filter because it filters out the blue of the "
"sky thus making the sky darker compared to clouds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "To convert a color photo to black-and-white:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:23
msgid "![image](images/Button-Black_and_White.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Black_and_White.markdown.txt:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.  Click the black & white tool button in the [tool\n"
"    bar](Tools-Editing.html). (A new black & white tool will appear at\n"
"    the top of the [tool stack](Tool_Stack.html).)\n"
"2.  To apply a colored filter, click in the color wheel. (For example,\n"
"    clicking somewhere in the yellow part of the color wheel applies\n"
"    yellow filter.)\n"
"3.  Adjust the Strength slider to increase or decrease the strength (and\n"
"    thus effect) of the tool.\n"
"4.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"
msgstr ""
"1.  Click the black & white tool button in the [tool\n"
"    bar](Tools-Editing.html). (A new black & white tool will appear at\n"
"    the top of the [tool stack](Tool_Stack.html).)\n"
"2.  To apply a colored filter, click in the color wheel. (For example,\n"
"    clicking somewhere in the yellow part of the color wheel applies\n"
"    yellow filter.)\n"
"3.  Adjust the Strength slider to increase or decrease the strength (and\n"
"    thus effect) of the tool.\n"
"4.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"

